		<head>
		<title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.eudoxus_rhodius.eudoxi_rhodii_fragmenta">
		EUDOXI RHODII FRAGMENTA
		</ref></title>
		</head>
			<div type="textpart" subtype="work">
			<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.eudoxus_rhodius.eudoxi_rhodii_fragmenta.historiai">
			ΙΣΤΟΡΙΑΙ
			</ref></title></ab>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="1">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.eudoxus_rhodius.eudoxi_rhodii_fragmenta.historiai:1">
					<bibl> Apollonius Mirab. c. 24:</bibl>
					<quote>
					Εὔδοξος ὁ Ῥόδιος Περὶ τὴν Κελτικὴν εἶναί τι ἔθνος φησὶν, ὃ τὴν ἡμέραν οὐ βλέπειν, τὴν δὲ νύκτα ὁρᾶν.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation"> Eudoxus Rhodius in Celtica regione gentem esse ait, quae interdiu non cernat, sed noctu videat. </note>
					<note type="commentary"></note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
			</div>
				<div type="textpart" subtype="book">
				<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.eudoxus_rhodius.eudoxi_rhodii_fragmenta.historiai.e_libro_nono">
				E LIBRO NONO
				</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="2">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.eudoxus_rhodius.eudoxi_rhodii_fragmenta.historiai.e_libro_nono:2">
						<bibl> Etym. M. p. 18, 57:</bibl>
						<quote>
						Ἀδρίας, τὸ πέλαγος. Διονύσιος· ὃς πρότερον ἐπὶ τῇ Ὀλυμπιάδι (Δ. ὁ πρότερος ἐπὶ τῇ ϟηʹ ὀλ.?) πόλιν ἔκτισεν Ἀδρίαν ἐν τῷ Ἰωνικῷ κόλπῳ, ἀφ ̓ ἧς καὶ τὸ πέλαγος Ἀδρίας καλεῖται. Εὔδοξος δὲ ἐν τῇ θʹ τῶν Ἱστοριῶν τὸ πέλαγος καὶ τὴν πόλιν ὀνομασθῆναι Ἀδρίαν φησὶν ἀπὸ Ἀδρίου τοῦ Μεσσαπίου Παύσωνος.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"> Adriaticum mare. Dionysius senior Adriam urbem ad sinum lonicum condidit; ab ea mare Adriaticum appellatur. Eudoxus vero in nono Historiarum libro Adriaticum mare nomen habere refert ab Adria Messapio, Pausonis filio. </note>
						<note type="commentary">Cf. Diodor. XV, 13. Theopompi fr. 140. — Praeterea Eudoxus Rhodius inter eos, qui in geographicis elaborarint, recensetur in Marciani Epitome Artemidori p. 63 ed. Hudson.</note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				</div>
